================================================================================
REVIEWED SUMMARY
================================================================================

C++ header:         include/emTreeDump/emTreeDumpFilePanel.h
C++ implementation: src/emTreeDump/emTreeDumpFilePanel.cpp

Purpose: emFilePanel subclass that displays a saved .emTreeDump file
inside a running Eagle Mode session. Owns an emTreeDumpRecPanel child
rooted at the tree's top node, which recursively creates child
emTreeDumpRecPanels for each node. The "render the dump as a zoomable
view inside the running app" workflow — a user can point Eagle Mode
at a .emTreeDump file and explore the captured tree in the same
zoomable UI that produced it.

Status: NOT PORTED — in-app dump-renderer subsystem out of scope for
the current dump-producer work (Phase 1 of
docs/superpowers/specs/2026-04-24-treedump-port-design.md).

This is the visual debug-renderer subsystem. The current Rust port's
emTreeDump work only produces .emTreeDump files; it has no consumer
for them in-app. Ported files are intended to be inspected either by
C++ Eagle Mode or by external tooling, not by a Rust renderer (which
doesn't exist).

Rust equivalent for now: none.

Future port path: ports together with emTreeDumpRecPanel,
emTreeDumpFileModel, emTreeDumpControlPanel, and emTreeDumpFpPlugin
if/when the in-app viewer is brought over. Depends on emFpPlugin and
emFilePanel being fully exercised for plugin-registered file types.
